This paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes an extension to the Random Forest algorithm to improve its predictive accuracy. Additionally, the use of an unsupervised learning technique (Local Outlier Factor) to identify diverse trees in the ensemble is a common approach in machine learning. The paper also involves outlier detection, which is a common topic in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Data Mining (cs.DM) sub-categories. The use of ensemble techniques and decision trees also suggests that this paper could belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the use of pruning to reduce the size of the ensemble is a common technique in Neural Networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
